HEADWORD: Atrabilious
<hw>At`ra*bil"ious</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Melancholic
or hypochondriac; atrabiliary.</def> <rj><au>Dunglision.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A hard-faced, <qex>atrabilious</qex>, earnest-eyed race.</q>
<rj><qau>Lowell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He was constitutionally <qex>atrabilious</qex> and scornful.</q>
<rj><qau>Froude.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Atramentaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
